    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-23T10:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-23T10:29:00-05:00" n="348"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vologda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-23T18:00:00+02:31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 23, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received March 24, 5.25 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Riggs,<note n="1" xml:id="d348fn1">Capt. <persName>E. Francis
                            Riggs</persName>, Assistant Military Attaché.</note> Moscow, wires
                        <persName>Ruggles</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d348fn2">Lieut. Col. <persName>James A. Ruggles</persName>,
                        Military Attaché.</note> to urge me to order six railway units to Vologda
                    immediately upon <persName corresp="#p_TL1">Trotsky</persName>’s request who
                    telegraphed same would be great accommodation and Riggs adds would be useful in
                    event of German advance which it is reported is being made in force in the
                    Ukraine. <persName>Ruggles</persName> indorses request. Have wired <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> through consuls Harbin, Vladivostok to
                    send six units to Vologda immediately and has [on his?] authority.</p>
                <p>Riggs states that French Military Mission has complied <persName corresp="#p_TL1"
                        >Trotsky</persName>’s request and assigned 38 French officers to assist
                    organizing new army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
